<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-14T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-14T18:00:00-05:00" n="1808" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1808">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 823.00/162.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">McMillin</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-14T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 14, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your May 13, 10 p.m. Glad to learn there are no threats of disturbances.
                            Use your influence to the uttermost to secure peaceful adjustment of
                            difference and establishment of government on per manent basis.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>